14 February 2006
Thanks to Jeffrey Mark Siskind, here are the steps for installing GTop on Debian:

# apt-get install libbsd-resource-perl
# apt-get install libgtop1
# apt-get install pkg-config
# apt-get install libgnome-dev
# apt-get install libglib1.2-dev
# apt-get install libgtop-dev
# cd /tmp
# tar zxf GTop-0.16.tar.gz
# cd GTop-0.16/
# perl Makefile.PL
# make
# make test
# make install